        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 16 at 4:02PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Redfield, or 10 miles west of Fort Scott, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marmaton, Uniontown, Redfield, Devon, Hammond, and Xenia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
